    "covariates": "Included: AGE, VPA, CBZ, CLBZ, LVT, fluoxetine, CLNZ, ethinyl estradiol, Age*CBZ",
    "observations": "Method of relating C/D ratio with covariates, after log transformation of C/D ratio. Does allow for dosing calculations, although the influence of weight is taken into account indirectly. No goodness-of-fit plots provided, making it difficult to determine model performance. Similar model to that reported by Reimers in 2005, but with focus on age.",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "Simplified PK",
    "equations": "Css=DOSE*exp(theta1+theta2*AGE+theta3*VPA+theta4*CBZ+ theta5*CLBZ+theta6*LVT+theta7*FLUOX+theta8*CLNZ+theta9*ESTR+theta10*CBZ*AGE) VPA/CBZ/CLBZ/LVT/FLUOX/CLNZ/ESTR=comedication (yes =1, no=0) with: valproate/carbamazepine/clobazam/levetiracetam/fluoxetine/clonazepam/ethinyl estradiol DOSE is in mg/d Css is in µmol/L, to convert to mg/L, do: Css*0.256091",
